842.jpg?resize=285,190 285w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/HE_20240706_07842.jpg?resize=320,213 320w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/HE_20240706_07842.jpg?resize=640,426 640w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/HE_20240706_07842.jpg?resize=800,532 800w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/HE_20240706_07842.jpg?resize=1280,852 1280w\"/\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003cspan\u003e‘Heart Eyes’\u003c/span\u003e\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003ccite\u003eChristopher Moss\u003c/cite\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\n\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\tThe Valentine’s Day-themed slasher film starring Mason Gooding and Olivia Holt, which came out in theaters in February, hails from Christopher Landon, the director of \u003cem\u003eHappy Death Day\u003c/em\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\tThe Heart Eyes killer always strikes on Valentine’s Day, killing couples in the most gruesome of ways. It’s up to Jay Simmonds (Gooding) and Ally McCabe (Holt), who have a somewhat frosty corporate meet cute at their jobs, to put a stop to the senseless killing of love stories and romance. They may just find their own in the process.\n\n\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\n\t\u003cstrong\u003e\u003cem\u003eSmile\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e – May 14\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n\n\t\t\t\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\t\n\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/MCDSMIL_PA015.jpg?w=300\" data-lazy-src=\"https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/MCDSMIL_PA015.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/MCDSMIL_PA015.jpg 3000w, https://deadline.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/MCDSMIL_PA015.jpg?resize=150,75 150w